text: I'm not bashing the movie because I thought overall it was a good one, but I just think it was a huge shame that the "fictional" part wasn't the whole movie. I know it's mostly from a book but I thought the "none fictional" part was ok at best and for me these parts took away from what could've been a masterpiece! Although I thought Adams as well as Gyllenhaal was great in the "none fictional" part, overall it took away from the momentum on which the other part build.  In the end, this movie was sadly a cock-teas in my opinion. I feel like I was robbed half a movie from seeing Tony (Jake Gyllenhaal), Detective Bobby (Michael Shannon) and Ray (Aaron Taylor-Johnson) who's rolls made this movie memorable.
